glft is a library that displays truetype fonts with OpenGL.
It uses vector fonts (aa with FSAA) and GL_ALPHA textures (AA using freetype engine).
it can automatically change the font size to the apparent size (autoscale).

author
Stephane Conversy, conversy@enac.fr, http://www.tls.cena.fr/~conversy
Nicolas Roussel
copyright (c) 1999-2004

license: gnu LGPL
see license.txt

Credits: important contributions were made by
Renaud Blanch
Jean-Rene Courtois

build:
mkdir ~/build/glft
cd ~/build/glft
~/src/glft/build/automale/bootstrap
./configure
make

test:
env GLFT_FONTDIR=/my/path/to/truetype/fonts demos/simple

install:
make install
